title: Raphael Warnock
added: Warnock is an advocate of policies to address climate change. He has stated that he supports the United States re-entering the [[Paris Agreement]], strengthening the [[Environmental Protection Agency]], and investing more into clean energy and green infrastructure.<ref>https://warnockforgeorgia.com/issues/climate/</ref>

title: Raphael Warnock
added: Though he has not endorsed the [[Green New Deal]], his 2020 Senate campaign was endorsed by the [[Sunrise Movement]], an organization that has called for sweeping changes to policy to fight against climate change.

title: Raphael Warnock

title: Raphael Warnock
added: ===Voting Rights===

Senator-elect Warnock has pledged to vote in favor of the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. He has also been outspoken in working towards making Election Day a federal holiday and expanding early and absentee voting.<ref>https://warnockforgeorgia.com/issues/voting-rights/</ref>

title: Raphael Warnock
deleted: U.S. Sen. Raphael Warnock (D-Ga.) is under investigation for voter fraud during his role serving as board chairman of a voter registration organization founded by Stacey Abrams. Warnock served as chairman of the board for the New Georgia Project in 2019, which is when election officials claim misconduct took place. The Georgia State Election Board voted 3-0 to refer the investigation to Georgia’s Attorney General Chris Carr, with the board’s lone Democrat joining Republican Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger in abstaining from the vote. [Forbes. Published February 11, 2021. https://www.forbes.com/sites/nicholasreimann/2021/02/10/georgia-sen-warnock-under-investigation-for-voter-registration-misconduct/?sh=67d2fffb6ea0]
